00:02:38.158 --> 00:02:40.660 position:50% align:center
- The 24th ward of Tokyo.

00:02:40.744 --> 00:02:43.246 position:50% align:center
Far eastern special
administrative region.

00:02:43.329 --> 00:02:45.874 position:50% align:center
A man-made island in Tokyo Bay.

00:02:45.957 --> 00:02:48.877 position:50% align:center
The allies ruled over
this island after the war

00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:51.046 position:50% align:center
but due to
its special circumstances,

00:02:51.129 --> 00:02:53.256 position:50% align:center
it became infamous as one
of the most dangerous

00:02:53.340 --> 00:02:55.091 position:50% align:center
red light districts in Asia.

00:02:55.633 --> 00:02:57.510 position:50% align:center
It's been 20 years since
they gave it back

00:02:57.594 --> 00:03:00.680 position:50% align:center
to Japan hoping to restore peace
and order to the island.

00:03:00.764 --> 00:03:02.682 position:50% align:center
After a transition period,

00:03:02.766 --> 00:03:04.476 position:50% align:center
it was about
to be officially incorporated

00:03:04.559 --> 00:03:06.144 position:50% align:center
as a part of Tokyo.

00:03:06.603 --> 00:03:09.272 position:50% align:center
However, because
of a particular incident,

00:03:09.356 --> 00:03:11.733 position:50% align:center
there's been a monumental turn
of events.

00:03:11.816 --> 00:03:14.152 position:50% align:center
[booming]

00:03:14.235 --> 00:03:15.362 position:50% align:center
- Wait a second.

00:03:15.445 --> 00:03:16.654 position:50% align:center
Are you telling me Asumi
went inside

00:03:16.738 --> 00:03:18.073 position:50% align:center
the building to save Kozue?

00:03:18.156 --> 00:03:21.034 position:50% align:center
- I attempted to stop her.
I told her to wait!

00:03:21.117 --> 00:03:22.827 position:50% align:center
- Aren't the firefighters
here yet?

00:03:22.911 --> 00:03:24.245 position:50% align:center
- I'm finding out right now.

00:03:24.329 --> 00:03:25.330 position:50% align:center
- No, it's no good.

00:03:25.413 --> 00:03:27.123 position:50% align:center
- They're in a gridlock.

00:03:27.207 --> 00:03:29.209 position:50% align:center
It's the festival.
[both exhale]

00:03:29.292 --> 00:03:31.503 position:50% align:center
- Mari, how long has it been
since Asumi went into

00:03:31.586 --> 00:03:33.588 position:50% align:center
the building?
- Like, three minutes.

00:03:33.672 --> 00:03:35.173 position:50% align:center
- I can save her.
I'm going in there.

00:03:35.256 --> 00:03:36.383 position:50% align:center
[buzzing]
[gasps]

00:03:36.466 --> 00:03:38.176 position:50% align:center
- You shouldn't be impatient,
Shu.

00:03:38.593 --> 00:03:40.929 position:50% align:center
I gotta figure out her location.

00:03:41.012 --> 00:03:43.390 position:50% align:center
Otherwise you'll just end up
missing each other.

00:03:43.473 --> 00:03:45.558 position:50% align:center
[buzzing]
- What about the coast guard?

00:03:45.642 --> 00:03:46.726 position:50% align:center
Aren't they here yet?

00:03:46.810 --> 00:03:48.061 position:50% align:center
Water spray should reach
the building

00:03:48.144 --> 00:03:49.312 position:50% align:center
from their fire boats.
- Shu?

00:03:52.357 --> 00:03:54.651 position:50% align:center
- I'd just tell him to wait.
- He's an idiot.

00:03:57.112 --> 00:03:58.405 position:50% align:center
- [panting]

00:03:58.863 --> 00:04:01.116 position:50% align:center
- Wait, Shuta!
The buildings have collapsed!

00:04:01.199 --> 00:04:02.450 position:50% align:center
- This is no time to talk!

00:04:02.534 --> 00:04:04.536 position:50% align:center
- Shu, hold on
for a little bit longer.

00:04:04.619 --> 00:04:06.996 position:50% align:center
I'm scanning with
the thermo sensor right now.

00:04:07.080 --> 00:04:08.373 position:50% align:center
- [groans]

00:04:10.041 --> 00:04:10.959 position:50% align:center
[blow lands]
- [shouts]

00:04:11.042 --> 00:04:12.669 position:50% align:center
- What are you--
[grunts]

00:04:12.752 --> 00:04:15.088 position:50% align:center
- Sorry.
Just can't sit still.

00:04:16.548 --> 00:04:18.466 position:50% align:center
[beeps, hisses]

00:04:18.550 --> 00:04:20.051 position:50% align:center
- Hold up, Shu!

00:04:20.135 --> 00:04:21.594 position:50% align:center
- Seriously?
Not you, too, Mari.

00:04:21.678 --> 00:04:22.762 position:50% align:center
- Go ahead.

00:04:22.846 --> 00:04:24.180 position:50% align:center
I--I won't stop you.

00:04:24.597 --> 00:04:25.890 position:50% align:center
Save both of them!

00:04:25.974 --> 00:04:29.144 position:50% align:center
- I will 'cause I am a hero.

00:04:29.227 --> 00:04:32.105 position:50% align:center
[thrilling music]

00:04:32.188 --> 00:04:39.112 position:50% align:center
♪ ♪

00:04:40.196 --> 00:04:41.531 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:04:42.323 --> 00:04:44.159 position:50% align:center
[panting]

00:04:44.242 --> 00:04:45.994 position:50% align:center
Hey, Kozue!
Where are you guys?

00:04:46.077 --> 00:04:47.328 position:50% align:center
Answer me!

00:04:47.412 --> 00:04:49.539 position:50% align:center
Mr. 24 is here to save you!

00:04:49.622 --> 00:04:52.083 position:50% align:center
Kozue!
Asumi!

00:04:52.167 --> 00:04:53.209 position:50% align:center
[flames roaring]
[gasps]

00:04:53.293 --> 00:04:54.836 position:50% align:center
Asumi, Kozue!

00:04:54.919 --> 00:04:56.546 position:50% align:center
[grunting]
Dammit!

00:04:56.629 --> 00:04:57.756 position:50% align:center
Either of you can hear me,
answer me!

00:04:57.839 --> 00:04:59.924 position:50% align:center
- Shu, over here!
Help!

00:05:00.759 --> 00:05:02.594 position:50% align:center
Shu!
- Kozue!

00:05:02.677 --> 00:05:06.097 position:50% align:center
Kozue, are you over there?
[shouting]

00:05:06.181 --> 00:05:10.727 position:50% align:center
[rumbling]

00:05:15.565 --> 00:05:18.943 position:50% align:center
[groaning]

00:05:19.027 --> 00:05:20.904 position:50% align:center
[exhales sharply]
Kozue.

00:05:20.987 --> 00:05:23.198 position:50% align:center
Are you all right?
Just sit tight.

00:05:23.281 --> 00:05:24.616 position:50% align:center
I'll move the rubble aside.

00:05:24.699 --> 00:05:25.617 position:50% align:center
- Shu.
- One moment.

00:05:25.700 --> 00:05:26.701 position:50% align:center
It'll be all right.
- Shuta.

00:05:26.785 --> 00:05:28.578 position:50% align:center
- What?
- She--

00:05:28.661 --> 00:05:31.581 position:50% align:center
everything fell and Asumi
shielded me with her body

00:05:31.664 --> 00:05:33.249 position:50% align:center
and now--
- Asumi.

00:05:34.834 --> 00:05:35.919 position:50% align:center
- [screams]

00:05:36.002 --> 00:05:37.837 position:50% align:center
Asumi!
Asumi!

00:05:37.921 --> 00:05:39.339 position:50% align:center
[grunting]

00:05:39.422 --> 00:05:40.465 position:50% align:center
Asumi!

00:05:40.548 --> 00:05:42.133 position:50% align:center
No way.
Please, no!

00:05:42.217 --> 00:05:44.511 position:50% align:center
- Shuta.
- I couldn't save her.

00:05:45.470 --> 00:05:48.306 position:50% align:center
- [exhales]
- I couldn't do it.

00:05:48.390 --> 00:05:50.975 position:50% align:center
I couldn't become a hero.

00:05:52.268 --> 00:05:53.728 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:05:53.812 --> 00:05:56.564 position:50% align:center
[phone beeping]

00:05:56.648 --> 00:05:58.942 position:50% align:center
Oh, man.

00:05:59.025 --> 00:06:01.277 position:50% align:center
What a horrific nightmare.

00:06:03.154 --> 00:06:05.073 position:50% align:center
[exhales]
[phone beeping]

00:06:06.074 --> 00:06:07.826 position:50% align:center
[groans]

00:06:09.703 --> 00:06:11.371 position:50% align:center
- You up?
- Yes, definitely.

00:06:11.454 --> 00:06:13.456 position:50% align:center
I'm awake.
We'll talk later.

00:06:13.540 --> 00:06:15.542 position:50% align:center
[groans]
[thuds]

00:06:15.625 --> 00:06:18.503 position:50% align:center
[phone beeping]

00:06:18.586 --> 00:06:19.838 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:06:19.921 --> 00:06:22.340 position:50% align:center
- You fell asleep again.
- No, I did not.

00:06:22.966 --> 00:06:24.384 position:50% align:center
- Doesn't matter.

00:06:24.467 --> 00:06:26.219 position:50% align:center
You better show up
to the memorial mass.

00:06:26.302 --> 00:06:27.220 position:50% align:center
- Yeah.

00:06:28.680 --> 00:06:30.682 position:50% align:center
He still acts
like he's my teacher.

00:06:30.765 --> 00:06:32.600 position:50% align:center
It's been so long
since I graduated.

00:06:32.684 --> 00:06:33.601 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:36.813 --> 00:06:38.106 position:50% align:center
It's such a bother.

00:06:38.690 --> 00:06:42.110 position:50% align:center
[water running]

00:06:42.193 --> 00:06:43.486 position:50% align:center
[grumbling]

00:06:43.570 --> 00:06:45.363 position:50% align:center
- Know how to tie one?
Need help?

00:06:45.447 --> 00:06:46.656 position:50% align:center
- Oh, you don't need to.

00:06:46.740 --> 00:06:48.033 position:50% align:center
Uh, dammit, Kiriko!

00:06:48.116 --> 00:06:49.909 position:50% align:center
- Hey, you call me Mom!
[fabric pulling]

00:06:49.993 --> 00:06:52.203 position:50% align:center
- [groans]
- Mm, how handsome!

00:06:52.871 --> 00:06:54.789 position:50% align:center
Shuta, have you grown
some more recently?

00:06:54.873 --> 00:06:56.583 position:50% align:center
Hey, come on, stop!

00:06:56.666 --> 00:06:58.877 position:50% align:center
- Maybe you're gonna grow taller
than your father now!

00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:00.045 position:50% align:center
- No.

00:07:00.503 --> 00:07:01.671 position:50% align:center
That's not gonna happen.

00:07:02.380 --> 00:07:04.341 position:50% align:center
Well, this'll be terrible,
but I'm gonna head over.

00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:05.592 position:50% align:center
- Hey, Shu.
- Huh?

00:07:05.675 --> 00:07:07.469 position:50% align:center
- Here, take it.
Breakfast.

00:07:07.552 --> 00:07:10.221 position:50% align:center
- Uh, I don't need any.

00:07:10.305 --> 00:07:11.973 position:50% align:center
- But it's fresh.
- I don't want it, though.

00:07:12.057 --> 00:07:13.058 position:50% align:center
- New product.

00:07:13.141 --> 00:07:14.392 position:50% align:center
- Hmm?
[bag rustling]

00:07:14.476 --> 00:07:15.602 position:50% align:center
[chomps]

00:07:15.685 --> 00:07:17.479 position:50% align:center
[chewing]

00:07:17.562 --> 00:07:20.065 position:50% align:center
It's not Danish, though,
but crunchy and fluffy,

00:07:20.148 --> 00:07:21.483 position:50% align:center
and the cream that's inside

00:07:21.566 --> 00:07:23.068 position:50% align:center
of this thing isn't simply
demi-glaze, either.

00:07:23.151 --> 00:07:24.277 position:50% align:center
[dog barking]
Huh?

00:07:24.361 --> 00:07:25.945 position:50% align:center
Oh, it's just you, Daisy!
Hello, there.

00:07:26.029 --> 00:07:27.614 position:50% align:center
[barking]

00:07:27.697 --> 00:07:29.449 position:50% align:center
Ah, sorry.
This has onions in it.

00:07:29.532 --> 00:07:30.617 position:50% align:center
I can't give you any.
- Shu!

00:07:30.700 --> 00:07:32.410 position:50% align:center
Hold Daisy!
Don't let her go!

00:07:32.494 --> 00:07:33.828 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:07:34.287 --> 00:07:35.914 position:50% align:center
[panting]
- [exhales sharply]

00:07:35.997 --> 00:07:37.832 position:50% align:center
Really, Mari?
- That was close!

00:07:37.916 --> 00:07:39.709 position:50% align:center
[laughs]
Thanks a ton, Shu.

00:07:39.793 --> 00:07:41.336 position:50% align:center
- [groans]
Taking her off leash

00:07:41.419 --> 00:07:43.505 position:50% align:center
is dangerous.
- It's not like that.

00:07:43.588 --> 00:07:45.924 position:50% align:center
We were talking back
at the house about taking Daisy

00:07:46.007 --> 00:07:47.425 position:50% align:center
to the vet.
She heard that,

00:07:47.509 --> 00:07:48.885 position:50% align:center
got scared,
then took off running.

00:07:48.968 --> 00:07:51.221 position:50% align:center
- You're going today?
- I am.

00:07:51.304 --> 00:07:53.431 position:50% align:center
Grandma hurt her back during
the karaoke tournament

00:07:53.515 --> 00:07:55.058 position:50% align:center
the other day
so it's up to me.

00:07:55.558 --> 00:07:56.559 position:50% align:center
Don't worry.
That's not until late afternoon.

00:07:56.643 --> 00:07:58.061 position:50% align:center
- Old Ume is injured again?

00:07:58.144 --> 00:08:00.438 position:50% align:center
- I didn't have time
to get ready because of Daisy

00:08:00.522 --> 00:08:02.023 position:50% align:center
so go on without me.

00:08:02.565 --> 00:08:03.983 position:50% align:center
- Okay.
Don't be late.

00:08:04.984 --> 00:08:07.529 position:50% align:center
- Same for you, Shu.
I want to see you at church.

00:08:07.612 --> 00:08:09.155 position:50% align:center
- I know!
I'll be there!

00:08:09.239 --> 00:08:11.866 position:50% align:center
- First time since graduating
that you're going

00:08:11.950 --> 00:08:13.868 position:50% align:center
to see Ran and Koki.
[exhales sharply]

00:08:13.952 --> 00:08:16.538 position:50% align:center
If only I could see RGB
in one place.

00:08:16.621 --> 00:08:19.290 position:50% align:center
Now, wouldn't that be something,
huh, Shuta?

00:08:19.374 --> 00:08:22.002 position:50% align:center
You three should swing by
after seeing Asumi.

00:08:22.085 --> 00:08:23.920 position:50% align:center
I'll save you a table.

00:08:24.379 --> 00:08:26.214 position:50% align:center
- You don't even know
if they're gonna show up.

00:08:26.297 --> 00:08:28.299 position:50% align:center
- Man, this place is deserted!
- [grunts]

00:08:28.383 --> 00:08:30.552 position:50% align:center
- Oh, and it's got
a cheap ass sign, too!

00:08:30.635 --> 00:08:32.303 position:50% align:center
- Pathetic strip mall
like this should just

00:08:32.387 --> 00:08:33.680 position:50% align:center
 declare bankruptcy and fold.
- This dump looks like

00:08:33.763 --> 00:08:35.015 position:50% align:center
it's over 30 years old.
- [spits]

00:08:35.098 --> 00:08:37.434 position:50% align:center
Seriously, call it quits.
- Mari,

00:08:37.517 --> 00:08:39.144 position:50% align:center
hold my breakfast a moment.
- Huh?

00:08:39.227 --> 00:08:40.937 position:50% align:center
Oh, hey, Shu!
- The fish I bought at that shop

00:08:41.021 --> 00:08:42.605 position:50% align:center
over there was rotten!
- What are you scabs lookin' at?

00:08:42.689 --> 00:08:44.149 position:50% align:center
Mind your business!
- Huh?

00:08:44.232 --> 00:08:46.317 position:50% align:center
- Hey, pocket.
- Huh?

00:08:46.401 --> 00:08:47.610 position:50% align:center
Pocket?

00:08:47.694 --> 00:08:50.155 position:50% align:center
What are you talkin' about, huh?

00:08:50.238 --> 00:08:52.323 position:50% align:center
- You dropped it.
- I wha--

00:08:52.407 --> 00:08:54.284 position:50% align:center
[grunts]
Are you, like, stupid?

00:08:54.367 --> 00:08:56.786 position:50% align:center
Does this look like a pocket
to you, little boy?

00:08:56.870 --> 00:08:57.871 position:50% align:center
- [exhales sharply]

00:08:57.954 --> 00:08:59.622 position:50% align:center
No, you do!

00:08:59.706 --> 00:09:03.126 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna turn your body into
a pocket ash tray!

00:09:03.209 --> 00:09:07.922 position:50% align:center
- [groaning]

00:09:08.006 --> 00:09:11.926 position:50% align:center
- You bastard!
[groaning]

00:09:12.010 --> 00:09:13.845 position:50% align:center
[all cheering]
- Mm?

00:09:13.928 --> 00:09:15.430 position:50% align:center
- Great job, Shu!
- As expected.

00:09:15.513 --> 00:09:17.098 position:50% align:center
- Hey Shuta.
Here, take this!

00:09:17.182 --> 00:09:18.141 position:50% align:center
- We really appreciate it,
Shuta.

00:09:18.224 --> 00:09:19.559 position:50% align:center
- Oh, wow.
Thanks a bunch.

00:09:19.642 --> 00:09:21.978 position:50% align:center
- Wow, this guy's toppled
so many stalls.

00:09:22.062 --> 00:09:23.605 position:50% align:center
- Resorting to violence again?

00:09:23.688 --> 00:09:25.440 position:50% align:center
- But don't guys
like that piss you off?

00:09:25.523 --> 00:09:26.900 position:50% align:center
- Hmm.

00:09:27.817 --> 00:09:30.195 position:50% align:center
That's true but I thought
you'd given up on being a hero.

00:09:30.278 --> 00:09:31.488 position:50% align:center
- Mm?

