the 24th ward within

00:10:35.301 --> 00:10:37.053 position:50% align:center
the next 24 hours.

00:10:37.137 --> 00:10:39.431 position:50% align:center
Please spread the word
and subscribe to our channel.

00:10:39.514 --> 00:10:41.099 position:50% align:center
DoRed!

00:10:42.308 --> 00:10:44.519 position:50% align:center
- Okay, then that's it!

00:10:44.602 --> 00:10:46.312 position:50% align:center
Amazing job.
Thanks for everything, Ran.

00:10:46.396 --> 00:10:47.939 position:50% align:center
- [exhales sharply]

00:10:48.023 --> 00:10:50.108 position:50% align:center
[groans]
I'm at my limit.

00:10:50.191 --> 00:10:51.693 position:50% align:center
So sleepy.

00:10:51.776 --> 00:10:53.111 position:50% align:center
Hey, Kinako.

00:10:53.194 --> 00:10:54.612 position:50% align:center
Could you please do me a favor?

00:10:54.696 --> 00:10:56.656 position:50% align:center
Put this data in the drone.
- Sure!

00:10:56.740 --> 00:10:58.575 position:50% align:center
- I'll do it for you.
- Hey, Kunai.

00:10:58.658 --> 00:11:00.493 position:50% align:center
- How are you doing, Kunai?

00:11:00.577 --> 00:11:01.953 position:50% align:center
Don't you have
to temporarily sever

00:11:02.037 --> 00:11:03.580 position:50% align:center
the cameras around
the train station today

00:11:03.663 --> 00:11:05.790 position:50% align:center
at some point?
- Preparations are complete.

00:11:05.874 --> 00:11:07.625 position:50% align:center
Kinako has it harder than me

00:11:07.709 --> 00:11:09.252 position:50% align:center
since there's so many
little things to do.

00:11:09.336 --> 00:11:10.879 position:50% align:center
- [giggles nervously]

00:11:10.962 --> 00:11:13.173 position:50% align:center
Honestly, that'd help out a lot
so I'm counting on you.

00:11:13.256 --> 00:11:14.341 position:50% align:center
- Yeah.
- Wow.

00:11:14.424 --> 00:11:15.550 position:50% align:center
Kunai is so kind.

00:11:15.633 --> 00:11:16.926 position:50% align:center
- Would you shut up, Lucky?

00:11:17.010 --> 00:11:19.137 position:50% align:center
- Hey, it's time to get going.
[all grunting]

00:11:19.220 --> 00:11:21.181 position:50% align:center
- Got it.
- Okay, Yamamori.

00:11:21.264 --> 00:11:23.141 position:50% align:center
- Let's all do our best,
everybody.

00:11:23.224 --> 00:11:24.934 position:50% align:center
- Come on, guys.
Hurry up.

00:11:25.018 --> 00:11:26.144 position:50% align:center
- Okey dokie.
- [snoring]

00:11:32.275 --> 00:11:34.110 position:50% align:center
- Hmm.

00:11:34.194 --> 00:11:35.904 position:50% align:center
[clattering]

00:11:35.987 --> 00:11:38.490 position:50% align:center
- There are two items on
the schedule today.

00:11:38.573 --> 00:11:41.618 position:50% align:center
Takara Elementary Fire
Memorial Service at 11:00.

00:11:41.701 --> 00:11:43.119 position:50% align:center
Opening ceremony
for the Kizuna Train at 3:00.

00:11:43.203 --> 00:11:45.622 position:50% align:center
- Kinako.
Energy drink me.

00:11:45.705 --> 00:11:47.207 position:50% align:center
- Oh, sure.

00:11:47.290 --> 00:11:49.417 position:50% align:center
[gulping]

00:11:49.501 --> 00:11:51.252 position:50% align:center
[exhales sharply]

00:11:51.336 --> 00:11:52.796 position:50% align:center
Give me some clothes.

00:11:53.922 --> 00:11:54.839 position:50% align:center
- Ran.

00:11:55.924 --> 00:11:57.550 position:50% align:center
Over-consumption
of energy drinks

00:11:57.634 --> 00:11:58.760 position:50% align:center
isn't good for your body.

00:11:58.843 --> 00:12:00.053 position:50% align:center
- Spend money
to make more money.

00:12:00.136 --> 00:12:02.222 position:50% align:center
- Huh?
- It's good business sense.

00:12:02.305 --> 00:12:04.099 position:50% align:center
The fastest way
to earn more money

00:12:04.182 --> 00:12:06.726 position:50% align:center
is to spend the money that you
can already get your hands on

00:12:06.810 --> 00:12:08.228 position:50% align:center
in a smart way.
- Hmm?

00:12:08.311 --> 00:12:10.814 position:50% align:center
- So because little old me wants
to create some energy,

00:12:10.897 --> 00:12:13.525 position:50% align:center
I borrow some energy in advance
to create more energy.

00:12:13.608 --> 00:12:15.777 position:50% align:center
Understand?
- [giggles]

00:12:15.860 --> 00:12:18.405 position:50% align:center
Don't you think that logic
is possibly a bit flawed?

00:12:18.488 --> 00:12:20.782 position:50% align:center
- I'm counting on you at
the train station today.

00:12:20.865 --> 00:12:22.826 position:50% align:center
- Okay.
[giggles]

00:12:22.909 --> 00:12:25.787 position:50% align:center
[upbeat music]

00:12:25.870 --> 00:12:30.875 position:50% align:center
♪ ♪

00:12:30.959 --> 00:12:33.128 position:50% align:center
- [yawning]
[phone buzzing]

00:12:33.211 --> 00:12:34.838 position:50% align:center
Huh?
- You awake?

00:12:34.921 --> 00:12:36.631 position:50% align:center
- Nah, I haven't slept.

00:12:36.715 --> 00:12:38.800 position:50% align:center
You know, you need to maintain
a more normal sleeping schedule.

00:12:38.883 --> 00:12:40.260 position:50% align:center
- Uh-huh.
Talk to you later.

00:12:45.515 --> 00:12:47.100 position:50% align:center
[door opens]
Excuse me.

00:12:50.645 --> 00:12:53.732 position:50% align:center
Father, after all
of the services are over today--

00:12:53.815 --> 00:12:56.359 position:50% align:center
- You should be aware that
the opening ceremony for Kizuna

00:12:56.443 --> 00:12:57.861 position:50% align:center
is this afternoon.

00:12:57.944 --> 00:13:00.363 position:50% align:center
We pushed ourselves
to ensure it would happen today.

00:13:00.447 --> 00:13:02.949 position:50% align:center
- Yes, that's why I don't mind
if it's after the ceremony,

00:13:03.033 --> 00:13:04.576 position:50% align:center
but if we could--
- I plan on dining

00:13:04.659 --> 00:13:06.411 position:50% align:center
with the governor
of Tokyo after that.

00:13:06.494 --> 00:13:08.413 position:50% align:center
- [exhales]

00:13:08.830 --> 00:13:11.499 position:50% align:center
- Mr. Koki, I will escort you.

00:13:12.083 --> 00:13:13.918 position:50% align:center
- [exhales]
Please do.

00:13:14.919 --> 00:13:16.546 position:50% align:center
- Tsuzuragawa.
- Yes.

00:13:16.629 --> 00:13:19.007 position:50% align:center
- In regards to moving up
our scheduled timeline

00:13:19.090 --> 00:13:20.925 position:50% align:center
for the system upgrade
of Hazard Cast,

00:13:21.009 --> 00:13:23.428 position:50% align:center
any issues?
- No.

00:13:23.511 --> 00:13:26.723 position:50% align:center
We're already at 80% progress
so it will be ready in time.

00:13:26.806 --> 00:13:29.851 position:50% align:center
I promise to share more
of the details with you later.

00:13:29.934 --> 00:13:30.977 position:50% align:center
- Please do.

00:13:31.394 --> 00:13:32.395 position:50% align:center
- Excuse me, sir.

00:13:34.606 --> 00:13:36.316 position:50% align:center
- Miss Tsuzuragawa,

00:13:36.399 --> 00:13:38.276 position:50% align:center
you're the manager
of development.

00:13:38.360 --> 00:13:40.570 position:50% align:center
Do you really have the time
to keep taking care of me?

00:13:40.653 --> 00:13:44.157 position:50% align:center
I accepted the development lead
under these conditions.

00:13:44.824 --> 00:13:47.285 position:50% align:center
- It picks at my self confidence
a little bit.

00:13:47.369 --> 00:13:50.121 position:50% align:center
- Please, don't worry about it.
[grunts]

00:13:50.205 --> 00:13:52.123 position:50% align:center
They're hiding among civilians,

00:13:52.207 --> 00:13:54.167 position:50% align:center
but S.A.R.G. members
are present.

00:13:54.250 --> 00:13:56.378 position:50% align:center
- We should check it out.

00:13:56.461 --> 00:13:57.879 position:50% align:center
I see.
You're right.

00:13:57.962 --> 00:13:58.922 position:50% align:center
Something might happen.

00:14:01.966 --> 00:14:03.009 position:50% align:center
Hmm.

00:14:03.093 --> 00:14:04.886 position:50% align:center
[tires squealing]
[cars banging]

00:14:05.804 --> 00:14:07.722 position:50% align:center
[all shouting at once]
- Please don't enter here!

00:14:07.806 --> 00:14:10.141 position:50% align:center
- Guide the traffic so that
we can shut down one lane!

00:14:10.225 --> 00:14:11.351 position:50% align:center
- We can still make it in time!

00:14:11.434 --> 00:14:12.936 position:50% align:center
- Running a red?

00:14:13.019 --> 00:14:15.605 position:50% align:center
- Well, this is quite
a speedy response.

00:14:15.689 --> 00:14:18.108 position:50% align:center
You don't have to join them
over there, Mr. Koki?

00:14:18.191 --> 00:14:20.276 position:50% align:center
- If an intern were to show up
on his day off,

00:14:20.360 --> 00:14:22.529 position:50% align:center
it would only cause trouble
for everyone involved.

00:14:22.612 --> 00:14:24.072 position:50% align:center
- I see.

00:14:24.864 --> 00:14:26.783 position:50% align:center
The victim seems
to be conscious.

00:14:26.866 --> 00:14:28.743 position:50% align:center
- Yes, a good outcome.

00:14:28.827 --> 00:14:31.246 position:50% align:center
Besides, the speed
of this response

00:14:31.329 --> 00:14:33.081 position:50% align:center
just demonstrates what
the Special Administrative

00:14:33.164 --> 00:14:34.624 position:50% align:center
Region Guard can accomplish.

00:14:35.291 --> 00:14:38.044 position:50% align:center
And yet this is only
a stopgap measure.

00:14:38.128 --> 00:14:39.963 position:50% align:center
We can predict crimes
but we can't arrest

00:14:40.046 --> 00:14:41.214 position:50% align:center
to prevent them.

00:14:41.297 --> 00:14:42.882 position:50% align:center
- We can't legally
charge anybody

00:14:42.966 --> 00:14:44.592 position:50% align:center
for their crimes until
they actually commit them.

00:14:44.676 --> 00:14:45.885 position:50% align:center
- Yes.

00:14:45.969 --> 00:14:47.846 position:50% align:center
The law has not caught up
with reality.

00:14:47.929 --> 00:14:49.723 position:50% align:center
At least not yet.
[phone buzzing]

00:14:49.806 --> 00:14:50.724 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
[phone clicks]

00:14:50.807 --> 00:14:52.642 position:50% align:center
Yes, hello?
- Hey, Koki.

00:14:52.726 --> 00:14:53.977 position:50% align:center
You're heading over, right?

00:14:54.394 --> 00:14:55.979 position:50% align:center
- Yes, I'm on the move.

00:14:56.062 --> 00:14:58.106 position:50% align:center
- You know what's going on after
the memorial?

00:14:58.189 --> 00:15:00.358 position:50% align:center
- Yes, I have
no conflicts there.

00:15:00.442 --> 00:15:02.360 position:50% align:center
I am bracing myself for it.

00:15:02.444 --> 00:15:04.029 position:50% align:center
- [chuckles]
Don't worry.

00:15:04.112 --> 00:15:05.405 position:50% align:center
Just try to stay loose.

00:15:05.488 --> 00:15:07.323 position:50% align:center
I'm sure you guys can handle it.
- [grunts]

00:15:07.407 --> 00:15:08.950 position:50% align:center
- I certainly hope so.

00:15:09.034 --> 00:15:11.202 position:50% align:center
- Talk to you later?
- Bye.

00:15:11.995 --> 00:15:14.164 position:50% align:center
- Is everyone headed over
to Miss Asumi's place

00:15:14.247 --> 00:15:15.999 position:50% align:center
in the afternoon?
- Yeah.

00:15:16.082 --> 00:15:17.542 position:50% align:center
- Will you need me?
- No.

00:15:17.625 --> 00:15:19.627 position:50% align:center
Mr. Shirakaba said he can drive.

00:15:19.711 --> 00:15:21.129 position:50% align:center
- The usual trio, then?

00:15:21.212 --> 00:15:23.506 position:50% align:center
- I'm not sure.
We'll see about that.

00:15:23.590 --> 00:15:24.883 position:50% align:center
- I'm worried.

00:15:25.550 --> 00:15:27.594 position:50% align:center
- Don't you dare.
Don't put one on me.

00:15:28.011 --> 00:15:29.262 position:50% align:center
- Right.

00:15:29.346 --> 00:15:30.889 position:50% align:center
- I don't want one
of those on me.

00:15:30.972 --> 00:15:33.016 position:50% align:center
- Of course.
- [scoffs]

00:15:33.516 --> 00:15:36.186 position:50% align:center
Don't even think about it.
- Right.

00:15:39.564 --> 00:15:41.483 position:50% align:center
I'll drop you off here
and head over after I find

00:15:41.566 --> 00:15:42.984 position:50% align:center
a place to park.
- Thanks.

00:15:43.068 --> 00:15:44.069 position:50% align:center
You helped me out a lot.

00:15:44.152 --> 00:15:45.612 position:50% align:center
I'll get home on my own, though.

00:15:45.695 --> 00:15:47.364 position:50% align:center
- Mr. Koki,

00:15:47.447 --> 00:15:50.867 position:50% align:center
Miss Asumi would pout if you
paid her a visit empty handed.

00:15:50.950 --> 00:15:53.286 position:50% align:center
- Indeed.
My mistake.

00:15:58.833 --> 00:16:00.251 position:50% align:center
A tracker.

00:16:00.877 --> 00:16:03.088 position:50% align:center
I guess at least it's not
a bug transmitter.

00:16:10.762 --> 00:16:12.347 position:50% align:center
Of course this happens.
[both groaning]

00:16:12.430 --> 00:16:14.432 position:50% align:center
- Sorry, why are you guys here?
- Uh, personal freedom,

00:16:14.516 --> 00:16:15.600 position:50% align:center
I suppose.
- More like,

00:16:15.684 --> 00:16:17.310 position:50% align:center
why did you think
we wouldn't be here?

00:16:17.852 --> 00:16:19.396 position:50% align:center
- Ah, right.
Of course.

00:16:19.479 --> 00:16:21.272 position:50% align:center
[grunts]
Mari!

00:16:21.356 --> 00:16:23.441 position:50% align:center
But how did she arrive
before I did?

00:16:23.525 --> 00:16:25.235 position:50% align:center
She set me up, didn't she?

00:16:25.318 --> 00:16:27.445 position:50% align:center
- I thought Kaba was acting
a bit too persistent.

00:16:27.529 --> 00:16:28.988 position:50% align:center
- Mari's in on it, too.

00:16:29.072 --> 00:16:31.366 position:50% align:center
This situation was bound
to happen sooner or later.

00:16:31.449 --> 00:16:33.034 position:50% align:center
Hey, hold up.
Shu,

00:16:33.118 --> 00:16:34.703 position:50% align:center
do you even realize how careless
you've been with your feet?

00:16:34.786 --> 00:16:36.996 position:50% align:center
- Huh?
Uh...

00:16:37.080 --> 00:16:39.165 position:50% align:center
- Do you really think
those shoes fit the occasion?

00:16:39.249 --> 00:16:41.835 position:50% align:center
- Uh, feelings, not fashion,
are what matter here!

00:16:41.918 --> 00:16:43.044 position:50% align:center
[both chuckling]

00:16:43.128 --> 00:16:46.006 position:50% align:center
[organ music playing]

00:16:46.089 --> 00:16:53.304 position:50% align:center
♪ ♪

00:16:53.930 --> 00:16:56.558 position:50% align:center
- May she rest in peace
under God's care.

00:16:56.641 --> 00:16:59.060 position:50% align:center
We shall put our hearts together
in prayer.

00:16:59.144 --> 00:17:00.854 position:50% align:center
- [inhales and exhales sharply]

00:17:00.937 --> 00:17:02.856 position:50% align:center
- Thus it is with great...
- Hey, guys.

00:17:02.939 --> 00:17:04.607 position:50% align:center
About this past year.

00:17:06.026 --> 00:17:07.610 position:50% align:center
No, never mind.

00:17:07.694 --> 00:17:10.071 position:50% align:center
- There isn't anything
to never mind about.

00:17:10.155 --> 00:17:11.865 position:50% align:center
- That's true.
We don't ever get together

00:17:11.948 --> 00:17:13.867 position:50% align:center
unless we have events
like this nowadays.

00:17:13.950 --> 00:17:15.493 position:50% align:center
- We will now begin

00:17:15.577 --> 00:17:17.912 position:50% align:center
the first anniversary
memorial mass

00:17:17.996 --> 00:17:21.207 position:50% align:center
in remembrance of the Takara
Elementary School fire.

00:17:21.291 --> 00:17:23.418 position:50% align:center
- It's been a year since
the incident.

00:17:23.501 --> 00:17:24.669 position:50% align:center
Because of it,

00:17:24.753 --> 00:17:27.964 position:50% align:center
we lost so many
irreplaceable lives.

00:17:28.048 --> 00:17:29.883 position:50% align:center
I myself have suffered
the painful loss

00:17:29.966 --> 00:17:31.468 position:50% align:center
of a family member.

00:17:31.551 --> 00:17:34.679 position:50% align:center
We possess irrefutable
scientific proof it was arson

00:17:34.763 --> 00:17:37.682 position:50% align:center
but we are still unable
to identify the perpetrator.

00:17:37.766 --> 00:17:40.935 position:50% align:center
It's all because of the fact
that there are no eyewitnesses.

00:17:41.019 --> 00:17:43.897 position:50% align:center
- Your dad really uses every
chance he gets, doesn't he?

00:17:43.980 --> 00:17:45.315 position:50% align:center
- I won't deny it.

00:17:45.398 --> 00:17:47.067 position:50% align:center
It's for good politics.

00:17:47.150 --> 00:17:48.693 position:50% align:center
- Please tell me
you don't blindly believe

00:17:48.777 --> 00:17:50.070 position:50% align:center
the stuff he's preachin',
do you?

00:17:50.153 --> 00:17:51.821 position:50% align:center
- [exhales]
- The basis of our efforts...

00:17:51.905 --> 00:17:54.616 position:50% align:center
- No, but the problem
is whether or not he's right.

00:17:55.533 --> 00:17:57.410 position:50% align:center
Anyway, are you heading over
after this?

00:17:57.494 --> 00:17:58.995 position:50% align:center
- Hmm?

00:17:59.079 --> 00:18:01.289 position:50% align:center
Kaba went on ahead
and set everything up already,

00:18:01.373 --> 00:18:02.374 position:50% align:center
right?

